336
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:05,410
Wait here. I'll get you some medicine.

337
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,220
Huaming, Huaming.

338
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:38,840
Come over quickly. I have an emergency.

339
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:16,500
Qin Gang

340
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:19,440
You're finally here.

341
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:21,500
Xinxin has a high fever of 40 degrees.

342
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,960
Should we take her to the hospital for an IV?

343
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:27,160
No need for an IV if there are no complications.

344
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,960
What did you give her for dinner?

345
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:29,480
Eggs.

346
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:32,760
Eggs can worsen fever symptoms.

347
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:35,890
How would I know? That's what I always ate.

348
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:37,180
What should we do then?

349
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,320
I made some porridge.

350
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,240
And some stir-fried vegetables on the side.

351
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,680
Remember, the food should be light,

352
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,940
but still nutritious.

353
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,300
What should we do next?

354
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,260
Give her medicine.

355
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,800
If that doesn't bring down the fever, try physical cooling methods.

356
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:57,570
How do you do physical cooling?

357
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,600
Come on, take your medicine now.

358
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:26,900
Drink more.

359
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:29,900
I can't drink anymore.

360
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:33,010
It helps reduce fever by sweating.

361
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,650
I'll drink it later.

362
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:12,050
It's physical cooling.

363
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:08,920
Huaming, Xinxin's fever has gone down.

364
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,320
Xinxin went to the supermarket.

365
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,160
There are some things I don't know how to do.

366
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:14,760
Could you come up and show me?

367
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:36,240
Is this right?

368
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:40,200
You can't mix it evenly that way.

369
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,530
Get the air bubbles out.

370
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:47,570
Give me the eggs.

371
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,160
Spread it along the edge of the pan.

372
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,240
So it cooks evenly.

373
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,920
When wiping the baby, first get him ready.

374
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,920
Then wipe with the tissue like this.

375
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:59,580
Support him like this. You can hold him this way.

376
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,680
Just add one more spoon of sugar.

377
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:06,010
Put some baby powder on him.

378
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:07,920
Like this.

379
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,600
These clothes...

380
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:14,570
Don't wash them with adults' clothes in the machine.

381
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,660
Keep them sealed in plastic bags.

382
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:20,160
Thank you.

383
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,140
Sorry for the trouble.

384
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:43,860
She's back.

385
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:48,330
Come on, wash your hands and let's eat.

386
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,800
Did you make all this?

387
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:00,540
Have a seat.

388
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,770
Try this soup first.

389
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:12,560
Taste it.

390
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:16,120
Did you cook all these dishes?

391
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:19,160
I'm learning how to cook.

392
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,880
I learn from TV shows and cookbooks.

393
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,380
Taking it step by step.

394
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:24,480
Try it.

395
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,050
The taste is off.

396
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:56,620
It's too salty.

397
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:00,500
Did you make this soup?

398
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:04,920
I'm learning to cook.

399
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:14,080
I don't really know much about cooking.

400
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,360
Just learning little by little.

401
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:21,640
I just want to make sure you eat and drink well.

402
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:23,500
And stay happy.

403
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:26,170
So the baby will be healthy too.

404
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:28,360
This is broccoli.

405
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:31,170
This dish may look simple, stir-fried broccoli.

406
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:32,160
It seems easy,

407
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,280
but it's actually quite tricky to make.

408
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,440
If you cook it for too short a time,

409
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,170
it stays raw.

410
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:39,080
And if you cook it too long,

411
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,040
it gets mushy.

412
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,040
So the timing has to be

413
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:42,840
just right.

414
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:44,540
Let me try it first.

415
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,250
I forgot to add salt.

416
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:51,290
I'll go add some.

417
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:42,500
Here, try it again.

418
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,120
Now it's good.

419
00:27:51,560 --> 00:27:51,960
Eat up.

420
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,880
Why are you still wearing an apron while eating?

421
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:58,480
It's fine. I'll be washing dishes after we eat.

422
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,800
No need. I'll do it later.

423
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,500
It's awkward eating with an apron on.

424
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,260
I just wanted you to rest a bit.

425
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:13,240
Let's eat.

426
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,160
Okay.

427
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:51,640
Why are you staring at me?

428
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:54,420
I'm not.

429
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:58,000
I just appreciate your recent changes.

430
00:29:01,760 --> 00:29:04,090
I just want to take good care of you all now.

431
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:06,480
I think if I work this hard,

432
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:10,440
I should do better than Huaming.

433
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:13,970
Why compare yourself with him?

434
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:15,800
You are you, and he is he.

435
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:19,140
I'm just making a comparison.

436
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:24,720
You must have seen all the things I've done.

437
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:26,800
I hope that someday,

438
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:28,530
you can give me another chance.

439
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,720
I don't know when it started,

440
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,580
but my life seems completely disrupted.

441
00:29:41,360 --> 00:29:42,960
I can't sort it out at all now.

442
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:45,960
Qin Gang.

443
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,640
Give me a little more time, okay?

444
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,200
I can wait patiently.

445
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:57,600
Just like you said,

446
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:00,700
we still have Xiaobao.

447
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:02,880
We're a family.

448
00:30:07,520 --> 00:30:08,480
Go ahead and eat.

449
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:10,920
I'll go clean up the kitchen.

450
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:31,800
Have a heart-shaped apple.

451
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:51,610
What's this?

452
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:54,920
The property management now requires

453
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,840
all tenants living in the apartment

454
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:57,960
to register.

455
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:01,800
What should I say?

456
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:04,080
What can you say?

457
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:06,680
Just say thank you and I'll say you're welcome.

458
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,240
Fine. Let's say I'm renting this place.

459
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:15,240
Then give me your bank account number.

460
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:16,840
When I have money,

461
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,640
I'll pay back all the rent to you.

462
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:19,660
No need.

463
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:22,170
You did what you thought you should do.

464
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,960
Now I need to do what I think I should do.

465
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:29,600
Okay.

466
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:33,890
Qin Gang.

467
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:37,160
For me,

468
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:43,240
I've lived in that house for almost three years.

469
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:46,040
Sometimes when there are just two people in this home,

470
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,160
I feel like

471
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,760
it's just a temporary place.

472
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,960
But when it's just the three of us,

473
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:55,720
you feel like it's a real home.

474
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:02,440
Thank you.

475
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,250
You're welcome.

476
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:19,720
Is it a mermaid?

477
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:21,360
The face should be toward me

478
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:22,890
and the tail toward the sea.

479
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:24,360
Don't touch my child.

480
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:26,700
I won't. I won't touch.

481
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,840
How did you know I was here?

482
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:54,040
The question I asked you last night,

483
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:55,500
have you thought about it?

484
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,960
Qin Gang, you know what?

485
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:02,660
Just now when I was standing here,

486
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:05,650
I remembered so many things from our past.

487
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:08,680
When I was at my lowest point,

488
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:10,400
I met him.

489
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:13,760
He built a small home for me,

490
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,120
taught me how to love.

491
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:18,720
But heaven played

492
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:20,240
a cruel joke on me.

493
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:25,720
I feel like I've aged so much lately.

494
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:27,640
Recently,

495
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:31,480
I suddenly feel like time is passing so slowly.

496
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:36,400
That day when you tried to kill yourself on the bridge,

497
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,090
I was really scared.

498
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:41,690
I suddenly became so afraid of losing you.

499
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:43,720
You know what?

500
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:46,880
We'll be family for life.

501
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:49,920
We'll raise our baby together.

502
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:55,530
But I don't have the capacity to love again right now.

503
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:58,540
Being together isn't about love.

504
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:01,920
It's about responsibility.

505
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:05,050
Huaming left his house to our baby.

506
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:10,780
Before he left, he was worried about how you'd be doing.

507
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:14,120
I now do laundry, cook,

508
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,239
clean the house, take care of our child -

509
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:17,900
all things Huaming taught me.

510
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,920
Sometimes when you weren't around,

511
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:26,280
those meals were actually cooked by Huaming.

512
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,130
When you had a fever,

513
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,560
he was downstairs

514
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:36,460
teaching me how to bring your temperature down.

515
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:39,440
He only left after your fever broke.

516
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:43,120
If I were to ask you now

517
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:44,360
to remarry me,

518
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,199
I would be truly selfish.

519
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:52,219
Huaming wasn't thinking about having you for himself.

520
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:54,639
He wanted you to be happy.

521
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:01,720
It's impossible between us now.

522
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,490
Nothing is impossible.

523
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:04,700
Xinxin,

524
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,480
I'm urging you to keep Huaming in your life.

525
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,160
Really,

526
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:14,170
it's over. That chapter is closed.

527
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:16,130
Come with me. Let's go find him.

528
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:28,040
You should at least say goodbye.

529
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:53,240
That's right.

530
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:56,160
Maybe it's difficult,

531
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,860
but for this possibility,

532
00:35:59,040 --> 00:36:00,700
maybe there's another ending

533
00:36:01,080 --> 00:36:02,610
that's worth fighting for.

534
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:05,460
You old fox.

535
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:08,450
I know you're doing all this

536
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:09,840
just to make me stay.

537
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:23,960
Where is the guest

538
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,360
who checked out already?

539
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:26,640
When did he leave?

540
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:28,080
I'm not sure about that.

541
00:37:08,680 --> 00:37:10,010
Where would Hua Ming go?

542
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:12,610
Forget it, Qin Gang. Stop looking.

543
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:13,800
Xinxin.

544
00:37:15,240 --> 00:37:16,080
If this time

545
00:37:16,080 --> 00:37:17,340
you don't see Hua Ming,

546
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:20,060
you might regret it for the rest of your life.

547
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,640
Think carefully. Where might he go?

548
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:26,530
He should be under the big banyan tree.

549
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:53,800
Xinxin.

550
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,360
When it comes to love,

551
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:57,880
I'm not a coward.

552
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:01,370
No one can stop us from being together.

553
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:03,800
I can risk everything for you

554
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:06,080
but I can't ignore our son's future.

555
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:10,620
Being separated from my daughter for so many years,

556
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:11,520
I know very well

557
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:13,400
that a broken family

558
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:15,640
causes irreparable damage to a child.

559
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:20,120
For our son to have a complete family in the future,

560
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,880
I have no choice but to leave.

561
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:23,560
